Title: Series: Four landscapes with the Holy Family on their Flight into Egypt
Description: Angels tending to the Holy Family. Mountainous landscape with an angel kneeling next to the Christ Child on the side of the road at centre, another looking on as Joseph helps the Virgin off the ass; proof before lettering; from a series of four plates Etching
Producer name: Print made by: Herman van Swanevelt
Curator's comments: This is one from a series of four, for comment see 1844,0425.15. This is first state, for an impression of second state of this plate, see S.2275.
Bibliographic references: Hollstein / Dutch and Flemish etchings, engravings and woodcuts c.1450-1700 (7.I)
Acquisition notes: 1844,0425.1 to 27 cost £145 8s 6d in total. Individual prices have been entered when known.
